## QA Validation Report: "Buy License" Button Implementation in CEP Login Modal

### Overall Verdict: **PASS**

---

### Requirements Checklist

| # | Requirement | Status | Details |
|---|-------------|--------|---------|
| 1 | "Buy License" link/button exists after Activate button | **MET** | Found at lines 739-741 in index.html |
| 2 | Links to "https://splice.video/pricing" | **MET** | `href="https://splice.video/pricing"` confirmed |
| 3 | Has `target="_blank"` | **MET** | `target="_blank"` attribute present |
| 4 | Has class `btn-buy-license` | **MET** | Class `btn-buy-license` applied alongside `btn btn-secondary` |
| 5 | Divider with "Don't have a license?" text | **MET** | Lines 736-738 contain `.login-divider` with exact text |
| 6 | `.login-divider` CSS class exists | **MET** | Lines 866-884 in style.css |
| 7 | `.login-divider` has flex styling | **MET** | `display: flex; align-items: center;` |
| 8 | `.login-divider` has centered text | **MET** | `text-align: center;` |
| 9 | `.login-divider` has border lines | **MET** | `::before` and `::after` pseudo-elements with `border-bottom: 1px solid var(--glass-border);` |
| 10 | `.btn-buy-license` CSS class exists | **MET** | Lines 887-903 in style.css |
| 11 | `.btn-buy-license` has gradient styling with #00D4FF | **MET** | `background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00D4FF, #0099CC);` |
| 12 | Hover state exists for `.btn-buy-license` | **MET** | Lines 900-903 define hover state |

---

### Detailed Findings

#### HTML Implementation (`/Users/imorgado/SPLICE/splice-cep/panel/index.html`)

**Login Modal Structure (lines 717-744):**
```html
<!-- Login Modal -->
<div id="loginModal" class="modal hidden" role="dialog" aria-modal="true">
    <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <h2>Login</h2>
            <button id="closeLoginBtn" class="close-btn">&times;</button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>Enter your license key to activate SPLICE</p>
            <!-- License key input and lookup fields -->
            <button id="saveLoginBtn" class="btn btn-primary">Activate</button>
            <div class="login-divider">
                <span>Don't have a license?</span>
            </div>
            <a href="https://splice.video/pricing" target="_blank" class="btn btn-secondary btn-buy-license">
                Buy License
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```

- The "Buy License" button is correctly positioned after the "Activate" button
- Uses an `<a>` tag (semantic for external navigation)
- All required attributes present: `href`, `target="_blank"`, `class`

#### CSS Implementation (`/Users/imorgado/SPLICE/splice-cep/panel/css/style.css`)

**Login Divider Styles (lines 866-884):**
```css
.login-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 16px 0;
}

.login-divider::before,
.login-divider::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
}

.login-divider span {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 0 12px;
}
```

**Buy License Button Styles (lines 887-903):**
```css
.btn-buy-license {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    text-align: center;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00D4FF, #0099CC);
    color: #000;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    transition: all 0.2s var(--ease-smooth);
}

.btn-buy-license:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
}
```

---

### Quality Observations (Beyond Requirements)

1. **Accessibility**: The button is properly keyboard-focusable as an `<a>` element
2. **Visual Hierarchy**: The cyan gradient (#00D4FF) provides good contrast against the dark theme
3. **User Experience**: The divider with text creates a clear visual separation between login and purchase options
4. **Link Security**: Opens in new tab (`target="_blank"`) which is appropriate for external navigation
5. **Responsive Design**: `width: 100%` ensures the button fills available space on different panel sizes

---

### Recommendations

None - implementation fully satisfies all requirements.

